HEADWORD: Petasus
<hw>Pet"a*sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from Gr.
<grk>pe`tasos</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. & Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>The
winged cap of Mercury; also, a broad-brimmed, low-crowned hat worn by
Greeks and Romans.</def>⟦br⟧
